</DOCHDR>
<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Poster5</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<P>
<CENTER>


<H1>Numerous inventions</H1>

<TABLE><TR><TD>
<IMG SRC="balloon.gif" WIDTH=250 HEIGHT=160>
</TD><TD>
<IMG SRC="boat.gif" WIDTH=250 HEIGHT=160>
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD><FONT SIZE=2>
Alfred Nobel supported Swedish engineer S.A. Andr&eacute;e's balloon expedition to the North Pole.  He suggested a number of improvements for this mode of transport: among others to treat the balloon fabric with a special varnish, but his ideas were never adopted.  The expedition of the balloon "The Eagle," came to a tragic end in 1897.
</TD><TD><FONT SIZE=2>
Alfred Nobel commissioned the first aluminum boat ever built (12 x 1.8 m), with a capacity of 25 to 30 passengers.  The boat, "Mignon," made its maiden voyage on Lake Zurich in 1891.
</TD><TR></TABLE>

<BR><BR>

<P><P>
<FONT SIZE=4>
"My home is where my work is, and I work everywhere".       <P>
<FONT SIZE=2></CENTER>
<P ALIGN=RIGHT>Alfred Nobel<P><BR><BR>

<P>

<CENTER><TABLE CELLSPACING=5><TR VALIGN=TOP><TD WIDTH=33%>

<FONT SIZE=5>R<FONT SIZE=3>ight up to his death, Alfred Nobel constantly worked in his laboratories.  His inventions were numerous.  Some of them were pure flights of fancy - projects that would never fly.  Other inventions of considerable importance were before their time, especially in the field of weapons technology (ballistite, the silent gun, ballistic rockets).  
  </TD>
<TD WIDTH=33%>
His<FONT SIZE=5> <FONT SIZE=3>research embraced many new fields offered by the fast-growing industrial society.

A goodly number of Nobel's inventions were of a peaceful nature and his research in synthetics was particularly important.  He developed substitutes for crude rubber and leather, as well as nitrocellulose-based varnishes.  He was involved in the production of artificial silk, took out a patent for the manufacture of perforated glass nozzles, 
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=33%>
and<FONT SIZE=5> <FONT SIZE=3>had the world's first aluminum boat built.   Nobel also designed a boiler which could withstand explosions.  He helped finance S.A. Andr&eacute;e's balloon expedition to the North Pole and also invested money in the manufacture of a bicycle  ("the Svea bicycle").

At his death, Alfred Nobel was the holder of 355 patents.

</TD></TR></TABLE>

</CENTER>

<HR><P>
<CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=75%><TR><TD WIDTH=33% HALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="poster4.html">[PREVIOUS POSTER]</A>
</TD><TD WIDTH=33% HALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="index.html">[TO INDEX]</A>
</TD><TD WIDTH=33% HALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="poster6.html">[NEXT POSTER]</A>
</TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER>
